article.headline: High Point 100, VMI 90
article.story: LEXINGTON, Va. (AP) -- Arizona Reid had 26 points and 15 rebounds and High Point built a second-half lead of 28 points before holding on to beat VMI 100-90 Thursday night. The Panthers (10-4, 3-1 Big South) led 55-40 at halftime and 74-46 with 15:53 remaining. But the Keydets (6-8, 1-2) closed to within nine with two minutes remaining and to within six with 50 seconds to go before High Point closed it out. Akeem Scott and Melvin Crowder added 15 points each for the Panthers. The Keydets were led by Reggie Williams with 34 points, Matt Murrer with 23 and Travis Holmes with 19. The rest of the team combined for just 14 points.
